  "texts": [
    "Ray-tracing using the lens equation (2) using your favorite deflection field α(θ) is easy and can be entertaining.",
    "2 Each pixel in the image plane is given the bright-ness of the corresponding pixel in the source plane.",
    "(Since β is a single-valued function of θ, but not the other way round, ray tracing is usually done backwards, from the observer's sky to the source.)",
    "Note that ray tracing in this way automatically preserves surface brightness (photons per steradian).",
    "A patch of uniform brightness on the source stays the same uniform brightness when lensed, but it can change in size and shape."
  ],
